02:04.592 --> 02:11.532
*

02:16.704 --> 02:18.639
- Excuse me.

02:18.672 --> 02:20.808
Are you serving breakfast yet?

02:20.841 --> 02:22.576
It's just that I'm starving.

02:22.610 --> 02:25.279
Not until 6:00.

02:25.313 --> 02:26.714
Do you know what, hon?

02:26.747 --> 02:28.616
They're setting up the buffet.

02:28.649 --> 02:31.752
Why don't you help yourself
to something off there?

02:31.785 --> 02:34.788
- Oh, that's great.
- Thank you.

02:34.822 --> 02:41.762
*

02:49.770 --> 02:52.506
Marshall.
What are you doing here?

02:52.540 --> 02:54.242
- Hey, this is
a funny coincidence.

02:54.275 --> 02:55.643
I deliver meat to this place.

02:55.676 --> 02:57.411
- But your meat is...

02:57.445 --> 02:58.846
- Poisoned?

03:00.581 --> 03:03.651
- I'm sorry
we couldn't help you.

03:03.684 --> 03:06.954
At sundown, we start our
three-day process of Restitution

03:06.987 --> 03:08.956
and you'll be in my prayers.

03:08.989 --> 03:11.392
- Little late for that now.

03:11.425 --> 03:13.361
Be sure and try the bacon.

03:14.728 --> 03:16.697
- I don't eat meat.

03:16.730 --> 03:18.432
- Well, but it's my meat.

03:18.466 --> 03:20.601
It'd mean a lot to me
if you did.

03:22.470 --> 03:25.506
- I suppose if I try it,
I can atone for it later.

03:25.539 --> 03:27.675
- You keep my secret,
I'll keep yours.

03:32.012 --> 03:34.982
Mm.
Mm.

03:35.015 --> 03:41.989
*

04:07.448 --> 04:14.388
*

04:26.500 --> 04:28.636
Sarah Lane outright blackmailed

04:28.669 --> 04:31.839
at least 15
current and former Meyerists.

04:31.872 --> 04:34.074
Now each one of these people
that wrote a check

04:34.107 --> 04:36.610
are hiding a secret.

04:36.644 --> 04:38.379
They have that secret on tape.

04:38.412 --> 04:40.748
If I can get a few of them
to come forward,

04:40.781 --> 04:43.384
we can shut
this whole thing down.

04:43.417 --> 04:44.685
- This is great.

04:44.718 --> 04:46.887
- Yeah.

04:46.920 --> 04:48.556
- What?

04:50.424 --> 04:52.726
- A bunch of immoral,
reprehensible people

04:52.760 --> 04:54.628
get to walk away scot-free.

04:54.662 --> 04:56.730
Secrets intact.

04:56.764 --> 04:58.466
- Must be hard.

04:58.499 --> 04:59.933
Be undercover like you are.

04:59.967 --> 05:02.470
Probably lose track
of up from down.

05:05.038 --> 05:07.007
- You just hope
you're fighting the good fight.

05:07.040 --> 05:09.009
Putting Sarah Lane behind bars

05:09.042 --> 05:11.679
so she can't take advantage
of people's trust?

05:11.712 --> 05:14.014
Sounds like a good fight to me.

05:17.050 --> 05:20.354
*

05:22.390 --> 05:24.558
- That's so cool.
- You're at NYU.

05:24.592 --> 05:26.827
- Yeah, I mean, it's just
a summer writing program.

05:26.860 --> 05:28.362
- Still.

05:28.396 --> 05:30.864
- I have to work, like,
four jobs for it, but...

05:30.898 --> 05:34.402
- But next year, you'll get in
for real, though, right?

05:34.435 --> 05:36.737
- Yeah, if I get a boatload
of financial aid.

05:36.770 --> 05:38.539
- You'll get it.

05:42.443 --> 05:44.945
- So that girl from the bus
last night...

05:44.978 --> 05:46.514
Is she your girlfriend?

05:46.547 --> 05:49.550
- No, no, she's... just a friend.

05:52.720 --> 05:56.023
Do you have a boyfriend?

05:56.056 --> 05:57.691
- Nope.

06:01.128 --> 06:04.031
Did you tell her who I am?

06:06.800 --> 06:09.403
How did you find me?

06:09.437 --> 06:11.839
- Um, your dad came
into the diner where I work

06:11.872 --> 06:14.107
and I asked where you were.

06:14.141 --> 06:15.876
- What was he doing there?

06:15.909 --> 06:17.845
- Just having coffee.

06:21.449 --> 06:24.918
- I haven't talked to him
in a while.

06:24.952 --> 06:26.887
- Yeah, he said that.

06:28.622 --> 06:30.491
- What else did he say?

06:30.524 --> 06:32.560
- Just that he misses you.

06:35.663 --> 06:37.598
- Um...

06:37.631 --> 06:40.501
I don't have a lot of time
today,

06:40.534 --> 06:43.637
but... would you...

06:43.671 --> 06:47.775
wanna get breakfast
with me or something?

06:48.876 --> 06:50.611
- Yeah, I'd love to.

06:56.584 --> 06:58.051
- It's a cute place.

06:58.085 --> 07:01.755
I don't know about that.

07:01.789 --> 07:04.091
- For a guy
who just got out of a cult.

07:05.659 --> 07:07.895
- Well, thank you,
then, I guess.

07:07.928 --> 07:10.130
- So my dad thinks
you're some kind of messiah now.

07:10.163 --> 07:12.032
Uh...

07:12.065 --> 07:16.169
- You know, crazy people get
what they think is stigmata.

07:16.203 --> 07:17.738
It's totally psychosomatic.

07:17.771 --> 07:19.248
I mean, when I was growing up
in The Movement,

07:19.272 --> 07:20.941
people left their bodies,

07:20.974 --> 07:22.976
they had all sorts of other
religious experiences.

07:23.010 --> 07:25.613
Even I did, but obviously,
it wasn't real.

07:25.646 --> 07:27.515
- No.

07:27.548 --> 07:29.182
I don't know
what happened to my back.

07:29.216 --> 07:31.652
You know, it could have
just been the wound.

07:31.685 --> 07:33.086
I don't know.

07:35.589 --> 07:37.224
- You know,
I've been thinking a lot

07:37.257 --> 07:39.927
about what you were saying,
and I think it's outrageous

07:39.960 --> 07:41.795
that no one in my family
has looked at me

07:41.829 --> 07:43.931
except for my dad
in over 20 years.

07:43.964 --> 07:45.265
- It is.
- I don't...

07:45.298 --> 07:47.200
How can you reject your kids
like that?

07:47.234 --> 07:49.937
- I don't know,
but imagine if 20 of us,

07:49.970 --> 07:53.073
ten of us, even,
walk onto that compound

07:53.106 --> 07:56.510
and say, we exist,

07:56.544 --> 07:59.613
we are not invisible,
we did not disappear.

07:59.647 --> 08:01.715
We are living, breathing
human beings

08:01.749 --> 08:03.917
with all the pain
they have caused

08:03.951 --> 08:07.588
to their sons,
daughters, mothers...

08:07.621 --> 08:09.557
- Ex-husbands.
- Yes, ex-husbands.

08:09.590 --> 08:11.859
But at least with me,
Sarah was willing

08:11.892 --> 08:14.094
to let me see the kids
after I left.

08:14.127 --> 08:17.798
You know, she will have our back
once we force the change.

08:17.831 --> 08:19.900
- You can't.
- You can't force the change.

08:19.933 --> 08:22.703
- Sarah can.
- She's co-guardian of The Light.

08:22.736 --> 08:24.805
- What? Really? Sarah?

08:24.838 --> 08:28.008
- Yeah, Sarah's the most devout
person that I know.

08:28.041 --> 08:29.276
- Really?

08:29.309 --> 08:31.845
- Yes, and she will be
the best thing

08:31.879 --> 08:33.614
that has happened
to The Movement

08:33.647 --> 08:36.049
once she gets out
from under Cal's influence.

08:36.082 --> 08:39.052
- Wow, Mom must love that.
- Her own daughter.

08:39.086 --> 08:41.221
They don't know anything,
you know.

08:41.254 --> 08:44.091
No one in my family has a clue
how two-faced they all are.

08:44.124 --> 08:45.964
- Tessa, slow down...
- You know, you're right.

08:45.993 --> 08:47.303
I'm gonna go in there.
I should go in there.

08:47.327 --> 08:49.062
And I should force them to look

08:49.096 --> 08:50.864
at the pain and the hurt
and the suffering.

08:50.898 --> 08:53.901
I should force them
to take a look at themselves.

08:53.934 --> 08:55.869
Guardian of the fucking Light!

08:55.903 --> 08:57.113
- You're right, you're right,
you're right.

08:57.137 --> 09:00.007
- But this needs to be done right.
- No.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.975
- We need to find others.

09:02.009 --> 09:04.845
We are more powerful as a group

09:04.878 --> 09:09.950
because this is about all of us,
the future of Meyerism.

09:09.983 --> 09:11.118
We need more time.

09:11.151 --> 09:14.622
- Fuck time.
- Okay?

09:21.161 --> 09:24.297
Fuck me.

09:24.331 --> 09:31.271
*

09:53.293 --> 10:00.233
*

10:06.273 --> 10:08.375
- Sarah?

10:08.408 --> 10:11.144
I'll be right there.

10:11.178 --> 10:18.151
*

10:18.185 --> 10:21.789
- We were amazing last night.

10:21.822 --> 10:23.156
On stage, I mean.

10:25.258 --> 10:29.730
But... the audience liked us,
I think.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.665
I felt...

10:31.699 --> 10:36.069
the doors opening.

10:36.103 --> 10:38.939
The people that will be
drawn to us

10:38.972 --> 10:43.811
as we leave some of the more...

10:43.844 --> 10:46.179
religious aspects
of Meyerism behind,

10:46.213 --> 10:50.150
focus more on individual growth.

10:54.755 --> 10:57.057
Hey.
How are you?

10:57.090 --> 10:58.258
- Tired.

10:59.860 --> 11:05.733
*

11:05.766 --> 11:06.934
Sarah.

11:10.437 --> 11:13.406
I feel good about this.

11:13.440 --> 11:15.408
Us.

11:15.442 --> 11:18.045
*

11:18.078 --> 11:20.013
- We should go.

11:32.525 --> 11:39.466
*

11:50.978 --> 11:53.113
- It's so god to have her back.

11:53.146 --> 11:55.849
- It sure is.

12:03.991 --> 12:05.993
- Okay, Mom,
please stop petting me.

12:06.026 --> 12:07.127
- Ha.
- I missed you.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.862
I'm allowed to miss you.

12:08.896 --> 12:12.265
- Hey, kiddo!

12:12.299 --> 12:13.400
Oh!

12:13.433 --> 12:14.534
How'd it go?

12:14.567 --> 12:15.803
- It was good.

12:15.836 --> 12:16.904
- Mm-hmm?
- Mm-hmm.

12:16.937 --> 12:19.006
- Mommy!
- I missed you.

12:19.039 --> 12:21.508
- Oh!
- How was the conference?

12:21.541 --> 12:23.777
- Great.
- Did they like you guys?

12:23.811 --> 12:25.278
- How could they not?

12:25.312 --> 12:26.880
Your mom is an inspiration.

12:26.914 --> 12:28.882
- I want details.
- I'll tell you later.

12:28.916 --> 12:30.951
- Where's your brother?
- I don't know.

12:30.984 --> 12:33.253
- Hey, Noa, where's Hawk?

12:33.286 --> 12:35.188
- He said he had to do something
in the city.

12:35.222 --> 12:36.924
He'll be here by sundown.

12:36.957 --> 12:38.525
I painted this for you.

12:38.558 --> 12:40.427
- Oh!
- For your Transgress.

12:40.460 --> 12:42.262
- Beautiful.
- Thank you.

12:42.295 --> 12:44.264
- Can you paint mine?
- Yeah.

12:44.297 --> 12:46.233
- Me too.

12:48.301 --> 12:51.438
- I hear the two of you were
on fire at the Faith Conference.

12:51.471 --> 12:54.441
- It was okay.
- Oh, it was more than okay.

12:54.474 --> 12:57.410
I think the audience
really responded.

12:59.847 --> 13:01.148
- Well, that's good to hear.

13:01.181 --> 13:04.217
We need to get our message
out there.

13:04.251 --> 13:07.287
How lovely.

13:07.320 --> 13:09.256
- Summer painted it.

13:13.060 --> 13:14.327
- She's very talented.

13:14.361 --> 13:15.595
Yeah.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.464
Mm.

13:17.497 --> 13:19.432
Fresh pine.

13:20.934 --> 13:23.904
It's too bad we burn them.

13:26.940 --> 13:28.876
*

13:28.909 --> 13:30.343
No one owns you.

13:30.377 --> 13:32.045
You own you.

13:32.079 --> 13:34.581
- I know.
- I know.

13:34.614 --> 13:36.917
- Are you allowed to talk
to people on the outside?

13:36.950 --> 13:38.385
- Yeah, of course.

13:38.418 --> 13:40.353
We talk to people
on the outside all the time.

13:40.387 --> 13:42.055
- So they wouldn't have
a problem

13:42.089 --> 13:44.557
that your mom is in town
visiting?

13:44.591 --> 13:47.227
- A lot of Meyerists choose
to cut off

13:47.260 --> 13:48.328
from their families, okay?

13:48.361 --> 13:50.030
I have not chosen to do that.

13:50.063 --> 13:53.100
- So why are you so worried?
- I'm not.

13:53.133 --> 13:54.902
You keep looking out the window.

13:54.935 --> 13:56.412
- Yeah, 'cause
we're talking about me leaving.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.071
- Are you not allowed to leave?

13:58.105 --> 14:00.207
- I can do whatever I want.

14:00.240 --> 14:01.574
- Is that so?

14:01.608 --> 14:04.011
- Yeah, I'm concerned
about Mary, okay?

14:04.044 --> 14:05.621
She doesn't know
I'm talking about all this.

14:05.645 --> 14:08.281
Your dad and I want
both of you to come home.

14:08.315 --> 14:10.183
We'll help in every way we can

14:10.217 --> 14:11.885
to take care of
Mary and our grandchild.

14:11.919 --> 14:14.021
- Yes, but this is about you,
Sean.

14:14.054 --> 14:15.555
What you want.

14:15.588 --> 14:18.491
You can't make
another person do something.

14:18.525 --> 14:22.595
Same way that the Meyerists
can't make you stay.

14:22.629 --> 14:25.432
No one has that power
over another human being.

14:25.465 --> 14:27.067
- Can you find a way to get Mary

14:27.100 --> 14:29.036
to sit down with Wendy
this afternoon?

14:29.069 --> 14:31.271
- No, we have to be
at the compound by sundown.

14:31.304 --> 14:34.207
- Why? What will happen
if you're not there by sundown?

14:40.013 --> 14:43.250
*

14:43.283 --> 14:45.618
So then when
he's about to take the poison

14:45.652 --> 14:47.955
that transforms him
into a beast,

14:47.988 --> 14:49.622
she breaks up with him.

14:49.656 --> 14:51.458
- Why?

14:51.491 --> 14:53.226
- So he doesn't have to
live as a beast.

14:53.260 --> 14:55.963
She knows that
being a beast sucks

14:55.996 --> 14:58.298
and he'd probably be happier

14:58.331 --> 15:01.234
living in the world he was
born into, in the human world.

15:01.268 --> 15:03.170
- That's sad.

15:03.203 --> 15:05.272
- Well, yeah, the assignment
was to write a tragedy.

15:08.508 --> 15:11.144
- It's kind of like
the story of us.

15:11.178 --> 15:14.647
Except you're not a beast.

15:14.681 --> 15:16.950
- You kinda saw me as one.

15:16.984 --> 15:18.385
- And you didn't
break up with me

15:18.418 --> 15:22.655
to save me from
the wild world of beastdom.

15:22.689 --> 15:25.125
- No.
- Why did you?

15:25.158 --> 15:31.131
*

15:31.164 --> 15:34.001
- I don't know.
- Things were really hard.

15:34.034 --> 15:38.405
*

15:38.438 --> 15:41.408
God, this view is incredible.

15:41.441 --> 15:44.477
*

15:44.511 --> 15:46.679
Restitution!

15:46.713 --> 15:50.550
Um, I... God, this always happens
when I'm with you.

15:50.583 --> 15:53.320
- What?
- I lose track of time.

15:53.353 --> 15:55.588
I'm supposed to be
at the compound by sundown.

15:55.622 --> 15:57.200
- I-I have to go.
- I mean, you're not gonna

15:57.224 --> 16:00.027
make it now.
Wait, am I gonna see you again?

16:00.060 --> 16:07.034
*

16:07.067 --> 16:09.502
You know what?

16:11.238 --> 16:14.507
I just watched my mom on stage

16:14.541 --> 16:16.743
at the World Faith Conference

16:16.776 --> 16:19.246
say all these things

16:19.279 --> 16:22.515
about self-love, and...

16:22.549 --> 16:25.485
they had nothing to do
with Meyerism.

16:25.518 --> 16:28.288
- Okay...

16:28.321 --> 16:31.024
I don't know what that means.

16:31.058 --> 16:37.997
*

16:39.499 --> 16:41.301
Wait, are you sure?

16:41.334 --> 16:43.636
- Yeah.

16:43.670 --> 16:50.610
*

16:56.283 --> 16:59.686
The most important
three days of our calendar year.

16:59.719 --> 17:01.454
We reflect,

17:01.488 --> 17:03.256
we re-act,

17:03.290 --> 17:06.259
and we relinquish.

17:06.292 --> 17:09.396
Cleansing our spirits
and our consciences

17:09.429 --> 17:12.632
for the contemplative months
of fall and winter ahead.

17:12.665 --> 17:14.701
- As we go into
the dark of night,

17:14.733 --> 17:17.637
we meditate
on our Transgressions.

17:20.740 --> 17:24.111
We locate
our transgressive actions

17:24.144 --> 17:28.348
for the past year that haunt us.

17:28.381 --> 17:31.184
We locate those we have hurt.

17:31.218 --> 17:35.088
We leave these vessels,
our bodies,

17:35.122 --> 17:39.426
and take the vessel
of the one we have caused pain.

17:39.459 --> 17:43.596
We live in the pain
that we have inflicted.

17:43.630 --> 17:47.134
We suffer as the sufferer does.

17:47.167 --> 17:50.137
*

17:50.170 --> 17:52.639
- My family.

17:52.672 --> 17:55.375
- Yes.

17:55.408 --> 17:58.311
- With my doubt.

17:58.345 --> 18:00.180
- Yes.

18:00.213 --> 18:03.583
*

18:03.616 --> 18:05.152
Take that on.

18:05.185 --> 18:12.125
* *

18:21.768 --> 18:28.708
*

18:38.718 --> 18:45.658
*

18:54.501 --> 19:01.441
*

19:02.509 --> 19:04.477
- Rest.

19:04.511 --> 19:07.180
Tomorrow we act.

19:07.214 --> 19:12.151
*

19:19.726 --> 19:26.666
*

19:39.279 --> 19:42.315
* *

19:42.349 --> 19:45.252
- Mrs. Small, I'm sorry
to barge in on you like this.

19:45.285 --> 19:46.619
- It's all right.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.588
- I tried to reach Marshall
on the phone.

19:48.621 --> 19:50.623
There was a service message.
It was disconnected.

19:50.657 --> 19:52.892
- He passed.

19:52.925 --> 19:55.328
Two weeks ago.

19:55.362 --> 19:57.764
Felt like he was sick forever,

19:57.797 --> 20:00.667
but then, when it came...

20:00.700 --> 20:03.770
*

20:03.803 --> 20:06.506
It came so quick.

20:06.539 --> 20:08.775
* *

20:08.808 --> 20:13.546
* Amazing grace

20:13.580 --> 20:17.817
* How sweet the sound

20:17.850 --> 20:22.355
* That saved a wretch

20:22.389 --> 20:26.793
* Like me

20:26.826 --> 20:30.263
* I once was lost

20:30.297 --> 20:32.265
- Sorry to keep you waiting,
Mr. Roberts.

20:32.299 --> 20:35.602
* But now am found

20:35.635 --> 20:36.969
* Was blind

20:37.003 --> 20:39.772
- First, please allow me
to express

20:39.806 --> 20:43.643
my deepest condolences
for the loss of your mother.

20:43.676 --> 20:46.346
Unfortunately,
the state requires us

20:46.379 --> 20:48.648
to fill out certain forms.

20:48.681 --> 20:50.550
I'll need your signature
in those places

20:50.583 --> 20:53.019
and I'll need to see
a form of ID.

20:53.052 --> 20:54.554
Driver's license is fine.

20:54.587 --> 20:56.723
It's purely a formality.

20:56.756 --> 20:58.425
Thank you, sir.

